Diagnosis. Distinguished from similar congeners by tip of procursus (distinctive membranous flap longer than sclerotized spine; 
Figs. 647, 648
), and shape of embolus (very similar 

S. peregrinus

but narrower in prolateral view and without pointed process; 
Fig. 649
); from 

S. peregrinoides

also by longer and more downward directed cheliceral apophyses (similar 

S. peregrinus

; cf. 
Figs. 614, 615
) and absence of v-shaped or u-shaped structure frontally in female internal genitalia (
Fig. 596
; epigynum and cleared female genitalia otherwise similar 

S. peregrinoides

and 

S. kalomo

).
